ney-mn0000029884}}\n* {{discogs artist}}\n* {{HWOF|Paul McCartney}}\n* {{Cite web |url=http://www.rupertandthefrogsong.co.uk/home.htm |title=Rupert and the Frog |accessdate=5 April 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20051124033713/http://www.rupertandthefrogsong.co.uk/home.htm |archivedate=24 November 2005 |url-status=dead  }} \u2013 Paul McCartney's animation 2005-11-24\n* {{IMDb name|id=0005200|name=Paul McCartney}}\n* {{tcmdb name|id=126288|name=Paul McCartney}}\n* [http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p009ml01 Paul McCartney] interview on BBC Radio 4 ''[[Desert Island Discs]]'', 26 December 1984\n* {{Facebook}}\n\n{{Paul McCartney|state=expanded}}\n{{Paul McCartney singles}}\n{{Navboxes\n| title = [[List of awards and nominations received by Paul McCartney|Awards for Paul McCartney]]\n| list  =\n{{Academy Award Best Original Score}}\n{{Brit British Male}}\n{{Gershwin Prize}}\n{{Grammy Award for Song of the Year}}\n{{Grammy Award for Best Score Soundtrack for Visual Media}}\n{{Grammy Lifetime Achievement Award}}\n{{Kennedy Center Honorees 2010s}}\n{{MusiCares Person of the Year}}\n{{Polar Music Prize}}\n{{1988 Rock and Roll Hall of Fame}}\n{{1999 Rock and Roll Hall of Fame}}\n{{Wolf Prize in Arts}}\n}}\n{{The Beatles}}\n{{Wings}}\n{{Paul McCartney family}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{Featured article}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mccartney, Paul}}\n[[Category:Paul McCartney| ]]\n[[Category:1942 births]]\n[[Category:20th-century classical composers]]\n[[Category:20th-century English singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century classical composers]]\n[[Category:21st-century English singers]]\n[[Category:Academics of the Liverpool Institute for Performing Arts]]\n[[Category:Anti-fracking movement]]\n[[Category:Beat musicians]]\n[[Category:Best Original Music Score Academy Award winners]]\n[[Category:Brit Award winners]]\n[[Category:NME Awards winners]]\n[[Category:British people convicted of drug offences]]\n[[Category:Capitol Records artists]]\n[[Category:Columbia Records artis