 of Sydney|Sydney Harbour ferries]]\n[[Category:Ferries of Australia]]\n[[Category:Sydney-related lists]]\n", "name_user": "Merbabu", "label": "safe", "comment": "fix error", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Sydney_Harbour_ferries"}
{"title_page": "List of Yes concert tours (2020s)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use British English|date=April 2020}}\n\n{{Main|List of Yes concert tours (1960s\u201370s)|List of Yes concert tours (1980s\u201390s)|List of Yes concert tours (2000s\u201310s)}}\n\nThe English [[progressive rock]] band [[Yes (band)|Yes]] has toured for five decades.\n\n== Yes's Spring 2020 North American Tour (cancelled) ==\nWith support from the [[Alan Parsons|Alan Parsons Live Project]] (except as indicated).\n\nOn 11 March 2020, Yes announced that they had cancelled their Spring 2020 U.S. dates and their appearances on the 7th \"Cruise To The Edge\" due to various factors including unavailable insurance coverage.<ref name=\"Yes cancelled Spring 2020 tour dates\">{{cite web |url=https://m.facebook.com/story.php?story_fbid=3904437936234832&id=223599747652021 |title=Yes has confirmed that they regretfully are cancelling a handful of shows and will not be performing on this year's \"Cruise to the Edge.\"|date= 11 March 2020 |website=Facebook |accessdate= 11 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! style=\"width:150px;\"|Date\n! style=\"width:200px;\"|City\n! style=\"width:200px;\"|Country\n! style=\"width:200px;\"|Venue\n|-\n! colspan=\"4\"| <s>Spring 2020 North American Tour</s> \n|- \n| <s>19 March 2020</s> || <s>North Charleston, SC</s> (Yes only) || rowspan=\"5\" | [[United States]] || <s>North Charleston Performing Arts Center</s> \n|- \n| <s>21 March 2020</s> || <s>SeaWorld Orlando, FL</s> (concert included with in-park admission) || <s>Bayside Stadium</s>  \n|- \n| <s>22 March 2020</s> || <s>Clearwater, FL</s> || <s>Ruth Eckerd Hall</s>\n|- \n| <s>24 March 2020</s> || <s>Jacksonville, FL</s> || <s>Florida Theatre</s>\n|- \n| <s>25 March 2020</s> || <s>Ft. Lauderdale, FL</s> || <s>Broward Center for The Performing Arts</s>\n|}\n\n== Yes's Cruise to the Edge 2020 (cancelled) ==\nOn 11 March 2020, Yes announced that they had cancelled their Spring 2020 U.S. dates and their appearances on the 7th \"Cruise To The Edge\" due to various factors including unavailable insurance coverage.<ref name=\"Yes cancelled Spring 2020 tour dates\"/>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! style=\"width:150px;\"|Date\n! style=\"width:200px;\"|City\n! style=\"width:200px;\"|Country\n! style=\"width:200px;\"|Venue\n|-\n! colspan=\"4\"|Cruise to the Edge 2020\n|-\n| <s>27 March \u2013 1 April 2020</s> || colspan=\"4\"|<s>Yes headlining the 7th \"Cruise to the Edge\" Prog Rock Festival</s><ref name=\"facebook Yes Cruise to the Edge 2020\">{{cite web |url=https://www.facebook.com/223599747652021/posts/2918207351524567/ |title= CRUISE TO THE EDGE 2020 ANNOUNCED / March 27\u2013April 1, 2020 |date= 23 April 2019 |website=[[Facebook]] |accessdate= 11 October 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n== Yes's Album Series 2020 Tour (postponed; to be rescheduled in 2021) ==\nYes were due to embark in Spring 2020 on their new tour entitled '''Album Series 2020 Tour'''. The show would have comprised two sets (with full production and a high definition video wall): the first set featuring a selection of favourite classic tracks from Yes's extensive catalogue and the second set featuring their 1974 ''[[Relayer]]'' (seventh studio) album in its entirety. The European leg was due to kick off on 24 April in [[Lisbon]], [[Portugal]] and end on 24 May in [[Leuven]], [[Belgium]] while the UK (& Ireland) leg of the tour was due to start on 26 May in [[Liverpool]] and end on 7 June in [[Dublin]], [[Ireland]] with a penultimate show on 5 June 2020 at the [[Royal Albert Hall]], [[London]], [[UK]].<ref name=\"facebook Yes Album Series 2020 UK Tour\">{{cite web |url=https://m.facebook.com/yestheband/photos/a.232253266786669/3384521251559839/?type=3 |title=UK TOUR ANNOUNCEMENT: THE ALBUM SERIES 2020 |date= 9 October 2019 |website=[[Facebook]] |accessdate= 11 October 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"yesworld.com Yes Album Series 2020 UK Tour\">{{cite web |url=http://yesworld.com/2019/10/the-album-series-2020 |title=The Album Series UK 2020 Tour: Relayer + Classic Cuts |date= 9 October 2019 |website=yesworld.com |accessdate= 11 October 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"yesworld.com Yes 24 European dates 2020\">{{cite web |url=http://yesworld.com/2019/10/yes-announces-24-european-dates-in-addition-to-uk-tour-for-the-album-series-2020/ |title=YES Announces 24 European dates in addition to UK Tour for The Album Series 2020 |date= 28 October 2019 |website=yesworld.com |accessdate= 28 October 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 20 March 2020, it was announced that the entire tour had to be postponed due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] and that it would be rescheduled in 2021.<ref name=\"facebook 20 March 2020 Yes\"/>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! style=\"width:150px;\"|Date\n! style=\"width:200px;\"|City\n! style=\"width:200px;\"|Country\n! style=\"width:200px;\"|Venue\n|-\n! colspan=\"4\"| Yes's Album Series 2020 Tour \u2013 European leg {{-}} (entirely postponed due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]; to be rescheduled<ref name=\"facebook 20 March 2020 Yes\">{{cite web |url=https://m.facebook.com/yestheband/photos/a.232253266786669/3933993063279319/?type=3 |title=YES regret to inform our fans that due to the Coronavirus Pandemic and our concerns about the safety of our fans, the forthcoming European and UK Relayer Album Tour Dates have been postponed to 2021. |date= 20 March 2020 |website=Facebook |accessdate= 20 March 2020}}</ref>)\n|-\n| <s>24 April 2020</s> ||[[Lisbon]]\n| [[Portugal]]\n| [[Campo Pequeno]]\n|-\n| <s>25 April 2020</s> ||[[Madrid]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Spain]]\n| [[Palacio Vistalegre|Box Vistalegre]]\n|-\n| <s>26 April 2020</s> ||[[Barcelona]]\n| Razzmatazz 1\n|-\n| <s>28 April 2020</s> ||[[Milan]]\n| rowspan=\"3\" |[[Italy]]\n| [[Teatro Dal Verme]]\n|-\n| <s>29 April 2020</s> ||[[Rome]]\n| Teatro della Conciliazione\n|-\n| <s>30 April 2020</s> ||[[Padova]]\n| Gran 