um in its entirety. The European leg was due to kick off on 24 April in [[Lisbon]], [[Portugal]] and end on 24 May in [[Leuven]], [[Belgium]] while the UK (& Ireland) leg of the tour was due to start on 26 May in [[Liverpool]] and end on 7 June in [[Dublin]], [[Ireland]] with a penultimate show on 5 June 2020 at the [[Royal Albert Hall]], [[London]], [[UK]].<ref name=\"facebook Yes Album Series 2020 UK Tour\">{{cite web |url=https://m.facebook.com/yestheband/photos/a.232253266786669/3384521251559839/?type=3 |title=UK TOUR ANNOUNCEMENT: THE ALBUM SERIES 2020 |date= 9 October 2019 |website=[[Facebook]] |accessdate= 11 October 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"yesworld.com Yes Album Series 2020 UK Tour\">{{cite web |url=http://yesworld.com/2019/10/the-album-series-2020 |title=The Album Series UK 2020 Tour: Relayer + Classic Cuts |date= 9 October 2019 |website=yesworld.com |accessdate= 11 October 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"yesworld.com Yes 24 European dates 2020\">{{cite web |url=http://yesworld.com/2019/10/yes-announces-24-european-dates-in-addition-to-uk-tour-for-the-album-series-2020/ |title=YES Announces 24 European dates in addition to UK Tour for The Album Series 2020 |date= 28 October 2019 |website=yesworld.com |accessdate= 28 October 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 20 March 2020, it was announced that the entire tour had to be postponed due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] and that it would be rescheduled in 2021.<ref name=\"facebook 20 March 2020 Yes\"/>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! style=\"width:150px;\"|Date\n! style=\"width:200px;\"|City\n! style=\"width:200px;\"|Country\n! style=\"width:200px;\"|Venue\n|-\n! colspan=\"4\"| Yes's Album Series 2020 Tour \u2013 European leg {{-}} (entirely postponed due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]; to be rescheduled<ref name=\"facebook 20 March 2020 Yes\">{{cite web |url=https://m.facebook.com/yestheband/photos/a.232253266786669/3933993063279319/?type=3 |title=YES regret to inform our fans that 